               <head>Shulkhan arukh (Oraḥ ḥayim) by Joseph Karo </head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>Parts of Shulkhan arukh. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="335v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Shulkhan arukh (Oraḥ ḥayim)</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">שלחן ערוך (ארח חיים)</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Includes the commentaries of Moses ben Tsevi Naftali Hirsch (Be᾿er ha-golah), in the upper part of the outer margin; Shetile zetim of David ben Shelomoh Mizrahi of Sana, on the outer side of the page; Revid ha-zahav, collected from the writings of David ben Shelomoh Mizrahi and his son Yahya; and Yahya Tsalih's Shoshanat ha-melekh. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folios 219r-225v embody sections from Hilkhot rosh ḥodesh of Mordekhai Yafe's Levush ha-ḥor (preceded by the compiler's introductory remarks on folio 218v). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The tables of Hezekiyah de Silva are given on folio 221v sqq. The part headed Ḥeshbon ha-teḳufot (folio 223r) appears to be taken from another source. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The number of sections in the entire work is 697. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/88686046">Karo, Joseph ben Ephraim</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/88686046">קרו, יוסף בן אפרים</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
